use_aes
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:100

    AES
    Introduced with Westmere (2010), not all 1st gen Intel CPUs have it.

use_avx
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:66

    AVX
    Normal Thorium baseline
    Present since Sandy Bridge (2011 2nd Gen. Core i series)
    and AMD Bulldozer (2012 AMD FX).
    Requires Windows 7 SP1 / Linux 2.6.30 or later to use.
    Uses new 128 bit registers and CPU blocks; a new era of SIMD.
    Includes AES and PCLMUL `-maes -mpclmul -mavx`

use_avx2
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:74

    AVX2 (x86-64-v3)
    Second generation AVX, expanded to 256-bit registers.
    Present since Haswell (4th Gen. Core i series), and
    AMD Excavator (4th Gen. refinement of Bulldozer cores) and 
    Zen (1st Gen. Ryzen).
    Includes FMA3 `-mfma -mavx2` (`-ffp-contract` see below at FMA section)

use_avx512
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:83

    AVX-512
    Third generation AVX, expanded to 512-bit registers.
    Present since Skylake (Specifically Skylake-X "Extreme Edition"
    processors), and AMD Zen 4 (4th Gen. Ryzen 7000).
    Only uses AVX-512 instructions common to all processors.
    `-mavx512f -mavx512cd -mavx512vl -mavx512bw -mavx512dq
     -mf16c -mlzcnt -mbmi2`

use_clang_cl
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/win/win.gni:16

    Whether to use the MSVC compatible clang-cl driver instead
    of the GCC style driver. Experimental.

use_common_controls
    Current value (from the default) = true
      From //build/config/win/win.gni:5

    Whether to specify to use modern common controls.

use_dwarf
    Current value (from the default) = true
      From //build/config/args.gni:34

    Whether DWARF debug info will be included in binaries.

use_fma
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:96

    FMA
    "Fused Multiply Add" operations
    Present since Haswell and AMD Piledriver (2nd Gen. refinement
    of Bulldozer).
    `-mfma -ffp-contract=fast` (use -mfma3 -mfma4 for Piledriver)

use_gtk
    Current value (from the default) = true
      From //build/config/linux/linux.gni:10

    Whether to include header dirs for GTK usage.

use_llvm
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/args.gni:24

    Whether to use LLVM compiler instead of GCC.
    Linux defaults to GCC, Mac defaults to LLVM.
    Windows can use either the GCC/MinGW or LLVM/MinGW toolchain.

use_lto
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/args.gni:42

    Whether to use Link Time Optimization (LTO)

use_mmx
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:103

    MMX, introduced with the Pentium MMX, only used if use_sse = false

use_neon
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:87

    arm32/arm64 specific: Whether to use NEON SIMD instructions.
    Part of the arm64 armv8-a specification

use_pdbs
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/win/win.gni:23

    Whether to enable .pdb debug information. Requires the clang-cl driver and
    is intended to take precedence over use_dwarf, but is not yet consumed by
    the toolchains.

use_qt
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/linux/linux.gni:13

    Whether to include header dirs for QT usage.

use_rpath
    Current value (from the default) = true
      From //build/config/linux/linux.gni:24

    Whether to use RPATH, to allow an executable to be relocatable.

use_sse
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:23

    SSE The first iteration of SSE, introduced with Pentium 3/Athlon XP

use_sse2
    Current value (from the default) = true
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:31

    SSE2
    Normal x64 compiler baseline, present since Willamette (Original
    2001 Pentium 4) and AMD SledgeHammer (1st Gen. Opteron) and
    the Athlon 64. Big step from MMX, x87, and SSE (i.e. SSE1)
    Baseline requirement to run Windows since update KB4103718
    for Windows 7 SP1/Server 2008 R2 SP1/Home Server 2011.

use_sse3
    Current value (from the default) = true
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:39

    SSE3
    Normal Chromium baseline, present since Prescott (2004 Pentium 4)
    and AMD SanDiego (2nd Gen. Opteron). x64 baseline.
    Only applicable to 32 Bit Windows and Linux builds, where
    setting it to false allows making an SSE2 build. (`-mmmx -msse2`)
    `-msse3`

use_sse41
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:48

    SSE4.1
    Normal PrimoBrowser baseline
    Normal ThoriumOS baseline because Core 2 Duo is the lowest
    hardware that other CrOS subsystems like drivers support.
    Present since Penryn (2007 45nm Core 2 Duo die shrink), and
    AMD Jaguar (2013 Athlon CPUs) and Bulldozer (2012 AMD FX).
    Includes SSSE3 since all SSSE3 `-mssse3 -msse4.1`

use_sse42
    Current value (from the default) = false
      From //build/config/simd/simd.gni:57

    SSE4.2 (x86-64-v2)
    Present since Nehalem (2009 1st Generation Core i series), and
    the same AMD CPUs as above.
    Normal LaCrOS baseline since Sept 2023.
    See https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=1475858
    Baseline for Windows since Windows 10 24H2.
    `-msse4.2`

